commit.message:
repr changed for datetime.timedelta in python 3.7

Update the expected string to deal with both old and new repr for datetime.timedelta.

see https://docs.python.org/3.7/whatsnew/3.7.html#changes-in-the-python-api
Fixed regexp for VCF Version 2.1

RRULE: Add workaround for dateutil<=2.7.2

https://github.com/dateutil/dateutil/commit/284622691f286a19fd51ec4f2aeeb08618dea266#diff-0cf96106a7dd4a241fca4079eac4c0a4

Revert "RRULE: always ignore time zone"

This reverts commit 8e281298b0ddd3d48e4698b73cd29bcd591d28cb.

The original behaviour was wrong. ``ignoretz=isinstance(dtstart, datetime.date)`` is always True, this causes vobject to always drop the time zone from UNTIL. If DTSTART has a time zone and UNTIL is UTC, the time zone of UNTIL gets replaced by the time zone of DTSTART without adjustment.

commit.message:
RRULE: always ignore time zone

dateutil raises an exception when UNTIL is UTC and ``dtstart`` is not set.
This restores the old  behaviour, because ``isinstance(dtstart, datetime.date)`` is always true.

commit.message:
ignore escaped semi-colons in UNTIL value

``line.value`` may contain escaped semi-colons (Ruby iCalendar library). This will influence the length of the UNTIL value, if it's not the last parameter.
